did.unittitle: Time Inc. Time Research Center Files: Subject Files
did.abstract: This finding aid contains only the detailed folder list of Series III. Subject Files for the purpose of in-depth keyword searching. Please make requests for the material from the complete version of MS 3009-RG 13.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This finding aid contains only the detailed folder list of Series III. Subject Files from the Time Research Center for the purpose of in-depth keyword searching.
Please make requests for the material from the complete version of finding aid MS 3009-RG 13.

did.unittitle: Series III. Subject Files

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Subject Files contain research materials related to common headline news topics that were used by reporters and researchers at magazines across Time Inc. Major topics covered include weapons and wars, geographic regions, populations of the United States and the Soviet Republic, domestic and international press organizations, United States elections, and word usage. Topics are frequently divided into sub-topics. For example, the files on New York City include boroughs, neighborhoods, government departments and agencies, parks, and extended folders on different streets.
Because these files were heavily used, there is some amount of misfiling.

The majority of materials within the Subject Files are magazine and newspaper clippings. Other types of materials include article correction, correspondent dispatches, correspondence between reporters, correspondence between reporters and editors, correspondence from the general public to magazine editors, transcripts of interviews and speeches as well as press conferences, summaries of interviews, editorial outlines for articles, government and foreign policy overviews, press releases, press kits, event schedules and programs, lists of contacts and committee members as well as research sources, lists of award winners, pamphlets, drafts of articles, academic and scientific papers, financial reports, photos, congressional reports, and factsheets.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Based on the original order, the Subject Files are organized alphabetically by topic then sub-topics. Multiple folders on the same topic or sub-topic are further organized in reverse chronological order.

scopecontent.p: The title of this folder refers to African-Americans and Afro-Russians who live and work in the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics as well as those who reported on its current events.
